.TH "touchscreen_parse_properties" 9 "touchscreen_parse_properties" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
touchscreen_parse_properties \- parse common touchscreen DT properties
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" touchscreen_parse_properties
.BI "(struct input_dev *input "  ","
.BI "bool multitouch "  ","
.BI "struct touchscreen_properties *prop "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "input" 12
input device that should be parsed
.IP "multitouch" 12
specifies whether parsed properties should be applied to
single-touch or multi-touch axes
.IP "prop" 12
pointer to a struct touchscreen_properties into which to store
axis swap and invert info for use with \fBtouchscreen_report_x_y\fP;
or NULL
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function parses common DT properties for touchscreens and setups the
input device accordingly. The function keeps previously set up default
values if no value is specified via DT.
